    <h2>What is GreenMel?</h2>
    <p>
        For the concerned parents in Melbourne who want to know the healthy evaluation of the suburb they live in, GreenMel is a website that provide the health evaluation of the suburb they live in. Unlike existing real estate websites such as Domain, GreenMel will concern on the health factors of suburbs and provide the integrated and accurate information for them.
    </p>

    <h3>1 Overview and Reason</h3>
    <p>
        Most people are concerned about their family members’ living environments. However, it is hard for them to find comprehensive resources that could information and suggestions based on those criteria.
    </p>
    <h3>2 Market category and target audience</h3>
    <p>
        The aim of the website is to provide an online platform that evaluate the suburbs in Melbourne from the healthy perspective. The main target users are the concerned parents, who want to know the health level of the suburb they live in. The health factors are number and location of sports facilities, hospitals, health clinics, parks and industry land use. GreenMel enables the users to get detailed information of the suburb’s healthy evaluation they live in.
    </p>
    <h3>
        3 Potential Sponsors?
    </h3>
    <p>
        The website is free of charge to use. Funding for the project will rely on the government and charity organizations. In addition, real estate affiliates might also be considered.   
    </p>
    <h3>
        4 Why GreenMel is important?
    </h3>
    <p>
        While discussing the topic of Health and Well-being, our team consider which problems that concerned parents might face. Our research indicates that people are very concerned about whether their living environment is healthy or not. Typical real estate statistics such as number of households, average income and living costs can easily be found, but it’s not as straightforward for health. Therefore, providing a platform that can provide such information can play a major role in helping concerned parents get more intuitive understanding of the suburb’s healthy level they live in.
    </p>
